               <msContents>
                  <summary> This complete copy of the <title>Taẕkirat al-Shuʻarā</title> (Chronicles
                     of Poets) by Dawlatshāh Samarqandī (d. ca. 1494) contains biographical accounts
                     of some 150 poets, together with selections of their poems. The author, from a
                     ruling Timurid-era elite family, dedicated this work to the cultural and
                     political figure <persName role="dte" ref="https://viaf.org/viaf/22198747/"
                        key="person_22198747">Mīr ‘Alī Shīr Navā'ī (d. 1501)</persName>. While
                     unsigned and undated, a purchase recorded on <date calendar="#Hijri-qamari"
                        from="1620" to="1621">1030 AH (1620–21 CE)</date> inscribed within the
                     volume would make this manuscrit the earliest of four copies held in the
                     Rylands. </summary>

                  <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_838-item1">
                     <author ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/79263034" key="person_79263034"
                        change="#ids-cleanup">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Dawlatshāh Samarqandī, d.
                           ca. 1494</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">دولتشاه سمرقندى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_20871" change="#ids-cleanup">Taz̲kirat
                        al-shuʻarāʼ</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_20871" change="#ids-cleanup">تذکرة
                        الشعراء</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="fa"><locus from="1b" to="1b"> برگ ۱پ (folio 1b):</locus>
                        تحمیدی که شاهباز بلند پرواز اندیشه بساخت فضای آن پرواز نتواند
                        نمود.</incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="fa"><locus from="307b" to="307b"> برگ ۳۰۷پ (folio
                           307b):</locus> از آن بیشتر که آوری بر ضمیر ولایت ستان باش و آفاق
                        گیر.</explicit>
                     <colophon>No colophon.</colophon>
                     <note>For other copies of this work in the Rylands collections, see <ref
                           target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_7036"><idno>Persian
                              MS 54</idno></ref>, and <ref
                           target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_6801">309</ref> and
                           <ref target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_6803"
                           >310</ref>.</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
